          content: "# HTML Forms and Input Elements\n\nHTML forms are essential for collecting user input. They're the primary way users interact with websites beyond just viewing content.\n\n## The <form> Element\n\nThe HTML `<form>` element is used to create an HTML form for user input:\n```html\n<form>\n  <label for=\"fname\">First name:</label><br>\n  <input type=\"text\" id=\"fname\" name=\"fname\" value=\"John\"><br>\n  <label for=\"lname\">Last name:</label><br>\n  <input type=\"text\" id=\"lname\" name=\"lname\" value=\"Doe\"><br><br>\n  <input type=\"submit\" value=\"Submit\">\n</form>\n```\n\n## The <input> Element\n\nThe `<input>` element is the most important form element. The `<input>` element can be displayed in several ways, depending on the `type` attribute.\n\n### Common Input Types\n\n#### Text Fields\n```html\n<label for=\"username\">Username:</label>\n<input type=\"text\" id=\"username\" name=\"username\">\n```\n\n#### Password Fields\n```html\n<label for=\"password\">Password:</label>\n<input type=\"password\" id=\"password\" name=\"password\">\n```\n\n#### Radio Buttons\n```html\n<input type=\"radio\" id=\"male\" name=\"gender\" value=\"male\">\n<label for=\"male\">Male</label><br>\n<input type=\"radio\" id=\"female\" name=\"gender\" value=\"female\">\n<label for=\"female\">Female</label>\n```\n\n#### Checkboxes\n```html\n<input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"vehicle1\" name=\"vehicle1\" value=\"Bike\">\n<label for=\"vehicle1\"> I have a bike</label><br>\n<input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"vehicle2\" name=\"vehicle2\" value=\"Car\">\n<label for=\"vehicle2\"> I have a car</label>\n```\n\n#### Submit Button\n```html\n<input type=\"submit\" value=\"Submit\">\n```\n\n### Other Input Types\n\n- `type=\"button\"`\n- `type=\"color\"`\n- `type=\"date\"`\n- `type=\"datetime-local\"`\n- `type=\"email\"`\n- `type=\"file\"`\n- `type=\"hidden\"`\n- `type=\"image\"`\n- `type=\"month\"`\n- `type=\"number\"`\n- `type=\"range\"`\n- `type=\"reset\"`\n- `type=\"search\"`\n- `type=\"tel\"`\n- `type=\"time\"`\n- `type=\"url\"`\n- `type=\"week\"`\n\n## The <label> Element\n\nThe `<label>` element defines a label for several form elements. The `<label>` element is useful for screen-reader users, because the screen-reader will read out loud the label when the user focus on the input element.\n\n```html\n<label for=\"fname\">First name:</label>\n<input type=\"text\" id=\"fname\" name=\"fname\">\n```\n\nThe `for` attribute of the `<label>` tag should be equal to the `id` attribute of the `<input>` element to bind them together.\n\n## The <select> Element (Dropdown List)\n\n```html\n<label for=\"cars\">Choose a car:</label>\n<select name=\"cars\" id=\"cars\">\n  <option value=\"volvo\">Volvo</option>\n  <option value=\"saab\">Saab</option>\n  <option value=\"fiat\">Fiat</option>\n  <option value=\"audi\">Audi</option>\n</select>\n```\n\n## The <textarea> Element\n\n```html\n<textarea name=\"message\" rows=\"10\" cols=\"30\">\nThe cat was playing in the garden.\n</textarea>\n```\n\n## The <button> Element\n\n```html\n<button type=\"button\" onclick=\"alert('Hello World!')\">Click Me!</button>\n```\n\n## Form Attributes\n\n### Action Attribute\nThe `action` attribute specifies the action to be performed when the form is submitted:\n```html\n<form action=\"/submit_data.php\">\n```\n\n### Method Attribute\nThe `method` attribute specifies the HTTP method to be used when submitting the form data:\n```html\n<form action=\"/submit_data.php\" method=\"post\">\n<form action=\"/submit_data.php\" method=\"get\">\n```\n\n### Target Attribute\nThe `target` attribute specifies where to display the response after form submission:\n```html\n<form action=\"/submit_data.php\" target=\"_blank\">\n```\n\n## Input Attributes\n\n### Required Attribute\nSpecify that an input field must be filled out:\n```html\n<input type=\"text\" name=\"username\" required>\n```\n\n### Placeholder Attribute\nSpecifies a short hint that describes the expected value of an input field:\n```html\n<input type=\"text\" placeholder=\"Enter your name\">\n```\n\n### Pattern Attribute\nSpecifies a regular expression that the input field's value is checked against:\n```html\n<input type=\"text\" pattern=\"[A-Za-z]{3}\" title=\"Three letter country code\">\n```\n\n### Min and Max Attributes\n```html\n<input type=\"number\" min=\"0\" max=\"100\">\n```\n\n### Step Attribute\n```html\n<input type=\"number\" step=\"10\">\n```\n\n## Form Validation\n\nHTML5 provides built-in form validation:\n```html\n<form action=\"/action_page.php\" method=\"post\">\n  <label for=\"username\">Username:</label>\n  <input type=\"text\" id=\"username\" name=\"username\" required minlength=\"3\" maxlength=\"20\">\n  \n  <label for=\"email\">Email:</label>\n  <input type=\"email\" id=\"email\" name=\"email\" required>\n  \n  <label for=\"age\">Age:</label>\n  <input type=\"number\" id=\"age\" name=\"age\" min=\"18\" max=\"100\">\n  \n  <input type=\"submit\" value=\"Submit\">\n</form>\n```",
          codeSnippet: "<!-- Create a complete registration form -->\n<form action=\"/register\" method=\"post\" class=\"form-container\">\n    <h2>Create Account</h2>\n    \n    <div class=\"form-group\">\n        <label for=\"username\">Username:</label>\n        <input type=\"text\" id=\"username\" name=\"username\" required minlength=\"3\">\n    </div>\n    \n    <div class=\"form-group\">\n        <label for=\"email\">Email:</label>\n        <input type=\"email\" id=\"email\" name=\"email\" required>\n    </div>\n    \n    <div class=\"form-group\">\n        <label for=\"password\">Password:</label>\n        <input type=\"password\" id=\"password\" name=\"password\" required minlength=\"8\">\n    </div>\n    \n    <div class=\"form-group\">\n        <label for=\"birthdate\">Birthdate:</label>\n        <input type=\"date\" id=\"birthdate\" name=\"birthdate\">\n    </div>\n    \n    <div class=\"form-group\">\n        <label>Gender:</label>\n        <input type=\"radio\" id=\"male\" name=\"gender\" value=\"male\">\n        <label for=\"male\">Male</label>\n        <input type=\"radio\" id=\"female\" name=\"gender\" value=\"female\">\n        <label for=\"female\">Female</label>\n    </div>\n    \n    <div class=\"form-group\">\n        <label for=\"bio\">Bio:</label>\n        <textarea id=\"bio\" name=\"bio\" rows=\"4\" cols=\"50\" placeholder=\"Tell us about yourself...\"></textarea>\n    </div>\n    \n    <div class=\"form-group\">\n        <input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"terms\" name=\"terms\" required>\n        <label for=\"terms\">I agree to the terms and conditions</label>\n    </div>\n    \n    <button type=\"submit\">Register</button>\n</form>",
