          content: "# CSS Fundamentals & Selectors\n\nCSS (Cascading Style Sheets) is used to style and layout web pages. It adds design, colors, and animations to your HTML content.\n\n## What is CSS?\n- **CSS** stands for Cascading Style Sheets\n- **CSS** describes how HTML elements should be displayed\n- **CSS** saves a lot of work. It can control the layout of multiple web pages all at once\n- **CSS** is added to HTML elements to define how they should look\n\n## How to Add CSS\n\n### 1. External CSS\nUse a `<link>` element in the `<head>` section:\n```html\n<head>\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"styles.css\">\n</head>\n```\n\n### 2. Internal CSS\nUse a `<style>` element in the `<head>` section:\n```html\n<head>\n  <style>\n    body {\n      background-color: linen;\n    }\n  </style>\n</head>\n```\n\n### 3. Inline CSS\nUse the `style` attribute directly in HTML elements:\n```html\n<h1 style=\"color:blue;\">This is a Blue Heading</h1>\n```\n\n## CSS Syntax\n\nA CSS rule consists of a selector and a declaration block:\n```css\nselector {\n  property: value;\n  property: value;\n}\n```\n\n- **Selector** - Points to the HTML element you want to style\n- **Declaration block** - Contains one or more declarations separated by semicolons\n- **Declaration** - Includes a CSS property name and a value, separated by a colon\n\n## CSS Selectors\n\n### 1. Element Selector\nSelects elements based on the element name:\n```css\np {\n  text-align: center;\n  color: red;\n}\n```\n\n### 2. Id Selector\nSelects a unique element with a specific `id` attribute. The id selector uses the hash character (#):\n```css\n#unique-id {\n  color: blue;\n  font-size: 24px;\n}\n```\n\n### 3. Class Selector\nSelects elements with a specific `class` attribute. The class selector uses a period character (.):\n```css\n.center {\n  text-align: center;\n  color: red;\n}\n```\n\n### 4. Universal Selector\nSelects all elements on the page:\n```css\n* {\n  margin: 0;\n  padding: 0;\n  box-sizing: border-box;\n}\n```\n\n### 5. Grouping Selector\nSelects multiple elements and applies the same styles:\n```css\nh1, h2, p {\n  color: blue;\n}\n```\n\n### 6. Descendant Selector\nSelects all elements that are descendants of a specified element:\n```css\ndiv p {\n  font-size: 18px;\n}\n```\n\n### 7. Child Selector\nSelects all elements that are immediate children of a specified element:\n```css\ndiv > p {\n  font-weight: bold;\n}\n```\n\n### 8. Adjacent Sibling Selector\nSelects all elements that are the adjacent siblings of a specified element:\n```css\ndiv + p {\n  color: red;\n}\n```\n\n### 9. Attribute Selectors\nSelect elements based on the presence of an attribute or attribute value:\n```css\n/* Has title attribute */\n[title] {\n  font-weight: bold;\n}\n\n/* title attribute starts with \"Btn\" */\n[title^=\"Btn\"] {\n  color: green;\n}\n\n/* title attribute ends with \"ton\" */\n[title$=\"ton\"] {\n  color: orange;\n}\n\n/* title attribute contains \"text\" */\n[title*=\"text\"] {\n  color: purple;\n}\n```\n\n### 10. Pseudo-classes\nUsed to define a special state of an element:\n```css\n/* Unvisited link */\na:link {\n  color: #FF0000;\n}\n\n/* Visited link */\na:visited {\n  color: #00FF00;\n}\n\n/* Mouse over link */\na:hover {\n  color: #FF00FF;\n}\n\n/* Selected link */\na:active {\n  color: #0000FF;\n}\n\n/* First child of parent */\np:first-child {\n  font-weight: bold;\n}\n\n/* Every element that matches every nth child */\np:nth-child(2) {\n  background: red;\n}\n```\n\n## Specificity\n\nIf multiple rules are defined for the same element, specificity determines which rule is applied.\n\nSpecificity hierarchy (highest to lowest):\n1. **Inline styles** (highest)\n2. **ID selectors** (#id)\n3. **Class selectors** (.class, pseudo-classes, attribute selectors)\n4. **Element selectors** (div, p, etc.)\n5. **Universal selector** (*)\n\n## CSS Comments\n\nComments are used to explain the code and are ignored by browsers:\n```css\n/* This is a single-line comment */\n\n/* \n  This is a \n  multi-line comment\n*/\n```",
          codeSnippet: "/* CSS Selectors Practice */\n/* Element selector */\nh1 {\n  color: #2c3e50;\n  text-align: center;\n}\n\n/* Class selector */\n.highlight {\n  background-color: #f1c40f;\n  padding: 10px;\n}\n\n/* ID selector */\n#main-content {\n  max-width: 800px;\n  margin: 0 auto;\n}\n\n/* Descendant selector */\n.navbar a {\n  text-decoration: none;\n  color: #3498db;\n}\n\n/* Pseudo-class */\n.button:hover {\n  background-color: #2980b9;\n  transform: translateY(-2px);\n}",
